The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     SPORT BRIEFS
                                                  Davydenko confirms participation  New Delhi: World No. 6, Russian Davis Cupper Nikolay Davydenko Wednesday confirmed participation in the $450,000 ATP Chennai Open to be held in Chennai from January 5 to 11 next year, says A Staff Reporter.  ldquo;I am very excited to play at the Chennai Open. The tournament has become very popular on the circuit. This is also my first visit to India so I am looking forward to playing here. I hope to make a good start to the New Year and improve my performance, playing in this tournament, rdquo; he said.  Roddick wins  Lyon: Top seed Andy Roddick reached the second round of the Lyon Grand Prix with a 7-6, 6-4 victory over Frenchman Nicolas Mahut on Tuesday.  The American, who is sixth in the race for the season-ending Masters Cup, began his bid to secure one of the three remaining places in the eight-man Shanghai field with a convincing win against the local favourite.  India prevail  New Delhi: India defeated China 3-2 to win the bronze medal in the seventh Asian Youth Boys rsquo; Volleyball Championship in Colombo on Wednesday. India beat China 25-21, 21-25, 21-25, 25-18 and 15-10. Thus India have qualified for Youth World Championship.  Chess meet  Hoogeveen: World junior champion Abhijeet Gupta outwitted International Master Wouter Spoelman of Holland to remain in joint lead with 4.5 points after the fifth round of the Essent International open chess tournament here. With his fourth victory in five games, Abhijeet shares the top spot with Alexandr Fier.   Laxman signs   London: Middle order batsman VVS Laxman has signed up for Lancashire and if the BCCI grants permission, the stylish Indian batsman will be available after the completion of the second leg of the IPL and will play for the English county side until the end of the 2009 domestic season.   Tigers lose   Ahmedabad: Ahmedabad Rockets thrashed Royal Bengal Tigers by 10 wickets in the ICL here on Wednesday.   Brief Scores: RBT 131 (B. Rao 4/15) vs AR 137/0 (Goodwin 61, Campbell 66). Ahmedabad Rockets won by 10 wkts.   Imran support   Karachi: Pakistan former captain Imran Khan Wednesday came out in support of national team coach Geoff Lawson, saying it is unfair to blame the Australian for all the ills in the team.   ldquo;I don rsquo;t think Lawson is solely responsible. The players should also take responsibility, rdquo; he said.
                                                                                                                                                                 
